AUXILIARY_DESCRIPTIONS.tractor-trailer: Vehicle used to transport undocumented aliens, also used for transporting commercial equipment and stopped at Freer, Texas on June 12, 2014; involved in an incident where contraband was detected by a dog and found to have ten undocumented aliens hidden in its closets and beds. On July 8, 2014, it was used by Raymond McMillon to transport Ramon De La Cruz and Jorge Miguel Hernandez-Gomez, who were discovered hidden in the tractor's sleeper area. Used in offenses for which Raymond McMillon was convicted and sentenced to 41 months' imprisonment. Involved in a search at Freer, Texas, where the consent of Zeba Williams was questioned. Searched with Raymond McMillon as a passenger claiming a possessory interest due to an agreement to help drive it for commercial purposes. Featured in a checkpoint video that showed unclear footage of its interior. Subject of a court case regarding a motion to suppress evidence from a checkpoint stop and search. Involved in a hearing on motions to suppress and for discovery of canine records. Used to transport aliens from an empty parking lot through Freer, Texas. Also involved in a conspiracy where aliens paid thousands of dollars to be smuggled into the United States. Used by Raymond McMillon to transport Ramon De La Cruz and Jorge Miguel Hernandez-Gomez after picking them up in an empty parking lot. Additionally, used to travel from San Antonio to Laredo to pick up commercial equipment. Stopped at Freer, Texas on June 12, 2014, with Zeba Williams driving and Raymond McMillon in the passenger seat. Involved in a stop where Agent Manuel Hernandez's dog alerted to the presence of contraband. Discovered to have ten undocumented aliens hidden in its closets and beds during a search by Agent Luis Pena. Used to transport Ramon De La Cruz and Jorge Miguel Hernandez-Gomez, who were discovered hidden in the tractor's sleeper area on July 8, 2014. Subject of a court decision affirming the district court's denial of Raymond McMillon's motion to suppress evidence from the checkpoint stop and search. Used by Raymond McMillon to transport aliens after they were picked up at an empty parking lot. Involved in a case where Raymond McMillon was convicted of alien transportation offenses and sentenced to 41 months' imprisonment. On June 12, 2014, it arrived at Freer, Texas with Zeba Williams driving and Raymond McMillon as a passenger. Involved in an incident where Agent Manuel Hernandez's dog alerted to the presence of contraband as Zeba Williams responded to a travel question. Used by agents to discover ten undocumented aliens hidden during a search. Involved in a motion to suppress evidence seized from the checkpoint stop. Subject of a challenge to the search that led to the discovery of aliens at Freer, Texas, with questions raised about the validity of Zeba Williams' consent due to the duration of the stop and the actions of Agent Luis Pena.
